  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "When you **deactivate remixd** and refresh the browser - the plugin **still** loads and so the modal pops up asking you to start the script.  \r\n\r\nThe problem to put it more generally - is that when remixd dies - in my case if my computer goes to sleep often ( but not always) remixd dies.  And I get the modal message that remixd has stopped.  I never know if I need to refresh Remix or just restart remixd.  \r\n\r\nSimilarly remixd cannot be stopped in the shell script with cmd + c.    \r\n",
